sources.title: Law of the Jungle (1942)
sources.description: Arline Judge joins a safari to escape the clutches of an enemy agent in this jungle adventure.

sources.title: Law of the Jungle (1942) MANTAN MORELAND
sources.description:
Stars: Arline Judge, John 'Dusty' King, Mantan Moreland
Director: Jean Yarbrough

A former member of a stranded theatrical troupe, earns a temporary living singing in a café in Duakwa, Africa. The café owner is secretly in league with two foreign agents with a goal of making the natives restless!

sources.title: DOUBLE FEATURE HELL 3 (it's a jungle out there)
sources.description: The adventure begins with coming attractions and a cartoon, followed by the first feature, "Law of the Jungle." The intermission featurette is chapter 11 of the serial, "Jungle Girl," followed by the second feature, "Forbidden Jungle." Vaccinations are not required for this safari. Flea powder is recommended for balcony seating. NOTE: The complete "Jungle Girl" serial is available on DVD from VCI Entertainment. All the other items in this simulation are found in various IA collections.

metadata.Plot: Nona Brooks, former member of a stranded theatrical troupe, earns a temporary living singing in a café in Duakwa, British Rhodesia, Africa. The café owner is secretly in league with two foreign agents with a goal of making the natives restless. American explorer Larry Mason leaves for the jungle with his servant, Jeff and a safari. Nona escapes the café into the jungle but is followed by the agents as, unknowing to her, she is carrying a report of the agent's activities. She joins the safari just as all hands are captured by a tribe of natives.
metadata.Actors: Arline Judge, John 'Dusty' King, Mantan Moreland
